What is a Procedure?
A procedure is a saved set of SQL instructions that performs one or more actions when called.

Key Points to Remember
1. It is Permanently Saved
  Once created, it stays in the database forever
  Closing the app or restarting does NOT delete it
  Only deleted when you manually drop it

2. It Lives in One Database
  Created in Database A → only works in Database A
  To use in another database → recreate it there or call with full name

3. It Runs Only When Called
  Does nothing on its own
  Only executes when you call EXEC procedure_name

4. It Can Perform Multiple Operations
  INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, SELECT all in one procedure
  No limit on how many operations
  Runs top to bottom in order

5. It Can Handle Errors
  Has TRY...CATCH block to handle errors gracefully

6. It Can Control Transactions
  Can COMMIT or ROLLBACK operations


What Operations Can It Do?
  Operations -: Insert Data, Update Data, Delete Data, Select Data, Error Handling, Transaction Control, Create/Drop Tables.

Basic Syntax -:
  -- Create
  CREATE PROCEDURE procedure_name
  AS BEGIN
    -- your operations here
  END;

  -- Call
  EXEC procedure_name;

  -- Delete
  DROP PROCEDURE procedure_name;


Golden Rules-:
   Procedure = Performs Actions
   Runs only when EXEC is called
   Saved permanently in the database
   Belongs to one database
   Can do unlimited operations
   Only disappears when you delete it

Real Life Analogy-:
  1. A Servant - Runs Only When You Tell
  2. A Cookbook Recipe - Permanently Saved, Reuse Anytime
  3. A Morning Routine - Multiple Tasks in One Go
  4. A Company Employee - Only Works in the Company it Belongs to



